      • getElementSenses

        Collection<Sense> getElementSenses()
        The senses of the elements in the synset. It is assumed that each element at least one of its senses is in this list. e.g., elementSenses[i] = elements[j].senses[k] for unique i,j,k
        Returns:
        The collection of senses
